Description:
Brand new and brilliant location
This brand new, stylish and exciting two storey home is situated within the heart of the magnificent Shearwater Estate in Cowes. Providing you with easy access to many of the lifestyle features the island is famous for. Just a short walk to Cowes golf course and the golden sandy beaches of Silverleaves. Close to playgrounds, parks and walking tracks making it the perfect location to enjoy your holidays or raise your family.
Locally built by GJ Gardner homes and colour selection by Darren Palmer, the home features large, open plan living and outdoor spaces, premium appliances and quality finishes throughout, six star energy efficiency including gas/solar hot water, double garage and situated on a 401 square metre corner allotment.
Suitable for permanent living or a brilliant investment opportunity for holiday or permanent rental. Contact us for an information pack detailing inclusions.

Description:
Ultimate privacy
Whether you are looking for a permanent residence, an investment opportunity or a holiday home look no further. Only one year old and backing onto farm land to ensure ultimate privacy, this three bedroom, light & bright home is impeccably presented throughout.
The master has a spacious walk through robe and master ensuite and the remaining two bedrooms are of a generous size and have huge built in robes. There are neutral colored tiled flooring and carpet throughout the living zones to ensure a modern look for years to come. The kitchen has loads of room to move around the island bench, a stainless steel cook top and a butlers pantry the size of a small study!
Additional features of the property include fans in all bedrooms, split system in the living zone, ducted heating throughout, quality blinds, double garage with ample storage, alfresco area ready to make your own and a clear run from the garage through to the backyard.
Inspection by appointment. Please call now to book in your time.

Description:
Entertainers Delight!
This attractive single level coastal home situated on a rare and fabulous dual entry allotment of approximately 1050 square metres provides a beautiful environment for absolute year round enjoyment. The home comprises a lovely and bright open plan kitchen, living and dining area featuring high ceilings and polished timber floors throughout as well as a large comfortable second living area. Large sliding doors from the main living space open onto an extensive north facing alfresco entertaining area overlooking the sparkling inground solar heated pool, plenty of lawn space and delightful landscaped gardens.
Perfectly located in Katherine Circuit, this incredible double allotment is on two separate titles with additional access from Chloe Close providing an amazing opportunity to further develop 14 Chloe Close or or enjoy the wonderful space as it is.
As you enter the resort style home you will immediately feel relaxed in this fantastic setting. Perfect for use either as a holiday retreat or for easy permanent living, the home offers a spacious floor plan with the master bedroom, including a walk in robe, ensuite and split system heating and cooling, located towards the front of the home while the remaining two bedrooms also boasting split system heating and cooling and family bathroom are situated to the rear.
The light filled kitchen boasts a stainless steel cook top and under bench oven, white dishwasher, ample bench space as well as a large pantry.
Providing a taste of the complete private luxury lifestyle, this surprising and exotic property is within close proximity to the superb beach and main shopping hub of Cowes.
This property for sale in Cowes, is proudly presented to you by Ray White Real Estate Phillip Island.

Description:
A Cut Above
A clever floorplan & contemporary design is stunningly presented in this Seagrove property.
Custom designed by award winning Beaumont Concepts, this home offers elements of style and sophistication that are uncommonly seen in this coastal market.
Situated high on the hill toward the back of the estate, with elevated views and uninterrupted bay views from the second story, the home has been well positioned to make the use of its generous 790sqm corner block. Eye catching landscaping, and a large welcoming entrance - commands attention from the street.
The perfect home for entertainers or large families, the ground level has been cleverly designed to make the most of the north facing aspect - bathing the living areas with natural light. The spacious open plan living, creates the hub of the home, whilst the well-appointed kitchen is centrally located, and boasts a large butler's pantry. A second living area serves as a great kid's TV room, 3 bedrooms (all featuring built in robes), family bathroom, separate toilet, and laundry complete this level.
A striking modern staircase leads to the upper level, where you will find the ultimate parents retreat. An open study sits at the top of the stairwell, perfect for a home office, which leads through to the substantial master bedroom, walk through robe, and lavish ensuite, complete with a freestanding bath. The views across to Shoreham and the bay from this level are captured through large windows, from both the bedroom and ensuite, and from the undercover sun deck - the perfect place to enjoy a peaceful morning coffee or sneaky afternoon wine!
Outside the undercover entertaining area features concrete benchtops and inbuilt BBQ with bench seating, large decked area, and cafe blinds for year-round use. Lush green lawns and low maintenance gardens allows plenty of room for the kids or the family pets. An oversized double garage provides secure off-street parking and can also be accessed internally from the home. A private side garden has been designed to hide the utilities area of bins, clothesline and vegetable garden
Other features include:-
Timber flooring throughout
Quality tiles
Stone bench tops
900mm appliances
Dishwasher
Split system heating / cooling
Rinnai gas heater
Nobo wall heater
NBN - fibre to the home
Reticulated gas
Outdoor shower
Walking distance from primary schools, shops, and the beach, this home would be ideally suited for permanent living - or as a spectacular holiday home!
The home truly demands inspection.
This property for sale in Cowes is proudly presented by Ray White Real Estate Phillip Island.

Description:
GREAT LOCATION HUGE POTENTIAL
Situated in a highly sought after location at the end of a quiet cul-de-sac, close to all the amenities that Cowes has to offer, this would make the ideal permanent home, holiday home, or a great addition to your investment portfolio.
This recently renovated 3 bedroom property is perfectly located within easy walking distance to the school, beach and the main shopping strip of Cowes.
As soon as you walk up the steps onto the front verandah and through the front door you will feel the sense of space on offer. High vaulted ceilings, with exposed beams that have been painted white, add a relaxed feel to the living zones. A large living, dining area is the central point of the home.
A recently renovated kitchen offers stainless steel appliances, ample storage, an island bench with added bench space as well as seating for informal meals. From the kitchen exit through the glass sliding door to the covered outdoor entertaining deck, complete with café blinds to provide the perfect entertainment area in all weather. The generously sized master bedroom has a walk through robe to a large ensuite with a bath. A further two bedrooms with built in robes, family bathroom and laundry complete the home. Split system heating & cooling units, ceiling fans in the bedrooms and living area, as well as a wood combustion heater provide year-round comfort.
The double garage has been converted into a second entertainment area, with bar area and room for a pool table. Ideal for all occasions or even just relaxing on a Sunday afternoon.
Set on approximately 970m2, with a fully fenced back yard, there is plenty of room shedding and boat or caravan storage.
With so many additional features, an inspection is a must, to see the true value and potential on offer here.

Description:
Beautifully chic and modern!
This remarkably private and modern townhouse located in the ever-popular Seagrove Estate offers not just a home, but a lifestyle. Within walking distance to the beach and main street of Cowes and overlooking the picturesque nature reserve.
The ground floor features an open plan dining and kitchen area which directly flows out to the north facing entertainment decking. The kitchen is complete with stone benchtops and stainless steel appliances . The master bedroom with walk in robe and ensuite, laundry and main living area are also on this level.
Upstairs comprises the remaining two bedrooms both with built in robes, one of which has access to the private balcony overlooking the lake and reserve and a modern bathroom complete with stainless steel fittings.
Other features include; double electric garage, carpet and tiles throughout, split system heating and cooling, gas log fire, built in barbecue on the entertainment deck, solar power system, low maintenance surrounds and side access for a boat/caravan.
All of this is set within a 322sqm approx. allotment. Inspections won't disappoint.

Description:
Central Location With Sea Views!
Situated in a brilliant central location in Cowes, only 800 metres from the pristine north facing Cowes bay beach, a rare opportunity awaits on a low maintenance 340sqm (approx) fully fenced allotment.
You will feel welcomed into your home featuring two fantastic light filled levels. The upper level boasts three good sized bedrooms, a family bathroom and an open plan kitchen, living and dining space that opens onto a north facing deck for you to enjoy all day sun with water glimpses while entertaining. The lower level features an impressive multi purpose room allowing for family/guest accommodation, games room, kids escape, the possibilities are endless!
Live the true island life enjoying shopping, restaurants and events in town or simply relax on the north facing bay beach just a short walk from your front door.
Other great features of the home include a double carport, storage shed, concrete driveway, fully fenced yard and split system heating and cooling. An Ideal solution for first home buyers, for use as a fabulous low maintenance holiday home or a great investment with a past permanent rental history.

Description:
A perfect home in a perfect setting!
Set over two levels is this immaculately presented home, located in a quiet and family friendly court and surrounded by permanent residences. This property is central to Cowes and offers a delightful northerly aspect - this gem is worth a look!
Upon entering the ground floor, you will find two robed bedrooms, main bathroom, laundry and a second living area.
The upstairs comprises of a spacious open plan living, kitchen and dining area, master bedroom with walk in robe and ensuite. For those who love to entertain, there is a front balcony which takes in the northern sun and a rear deck overlooking the beautiful gardens.
With other great features including polished timber floors, carpet and tiles throughout, split system heating and cooling, high ceilings, ample storage, outside shower, water tank, carport and double garage complete with lights and power. There is also extra off-street parking at the front of the home for your guests.
All of this is set within a 676sqm approx. allotment with lovely established surrounds and is within a short stroll to the RSL, Primary Schools, Doctors, Shops and Blue Gum Reserve.

Description:
Timeless Family Living!
Super spacious and offering a wonderful balance of indoor and outdoor living, this family home is sure to tick all of your boxes.
With two separate living spaces, the split-level design is perfect for growing families and lends itself to permanent living or use as a holiday home. The mezzanine living area with raked ceilings provides a character filled space to relax in, while the downstairs rumpus/games room features beautiful timber floors. The modern kitchen features stainless steel appliances and overlooks the adjacent dining area. Two split systems and combustion heating ensure year-round comfort.
Opening from the upstairs living space is a covered deck that offers glimpses to Westernport Bay, while a second deck to the rear provides a larger entertaining space that's ideal for the warmer months.
A 700m2 parcel of land is enhanced by low maintenance gardens and a location that places you within walking distance to shops, cafes and primary schools. This property is offered fully furnished, meaning you can move in straight away and enjoy the Island lifestyle.
Book your inspection before it's too late!
